Request   : I want to create 2  mini tools that mirror actual tools I have. Each tool is around 10 cm long. I also want to create and a box to store them.

APPROVED PLAN
-------------
Step 1: Fusion 360
Design the two mini tools (10 cm long each) and the custom storage box.
Duration: 3h - Booking required: No

Step 2: PreForm
Prepare the 3D models (mini tools and box) for SLA printing, including orienting parts and adding necessary supports.
Duration: 1h - Booking required: No

Step 3: SLA 3D Printer
Print the two mini tools and the storage box using the SLA 3D Printer for high detail.
Duration: 8h - Booking required: Yes

Step 4: UV Curing Station
Post-cure the SLA printed parts to achieve final material properties and strength.
Duration: 1h - Booking required: Yes

Step 5: Support Removal Tools
Carefully remove the printing supports from the mini tools and the storage box.
Duration: 1h - Booking required: No

Step 6: Sanding & Polishing Tools
Sand and polish the surfaces of the mini tools and the box to achieve a smooth finish.
Duration: 2h - Booking required: No

Step 7: Calipers
Inspect the printed mini tools and box to ensure they meet the desired dimensions and specifications.
Duration: 0.25h - Booking required: No


